    {
      "id": "5e835f86a947762aaaead92bc170d8ffb8ae80fc",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-12-31 00:05:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI was going to complain about this patch because the bufffred IO would add two data copies for every page, but I see it is now abandoned. \n\nOne thing I did notice is that the buffer size for the O_DIRECT IO is probably too small to get good performance anyway. It is stripe_size, or 1MB if that can't be found. I'd expect at least 32MB is needed for O_DIRECT to get good performance.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
